Merge pull request #449 from can-keklik/next

Fix for fetch.js fetchEvents function

Fix for fetch.js fetchEvents function
The former version omits the JSON parse exceptions. Since the type of "params.qstring.events" still a string after the parse attempt, the if block doesn't get executed, and the function exits silently. Naturally, the system doesn't generate a response for requests that contain bad "events" querystring, and leads to a timeout.

Refresh problem fix on view change

Each view is refreshed by new data from server every 10 seconds. If view
is changed (from Sessions to Users for ex.) at the end of this 10
seconds, refresh had some weird effects. Fix involves an update to each
view's refresh function to check whether the active view is the current
function's view itself.
